2.1 Core Hypothesis

All human production is already machine-assisted; therefore, isolating AI as a distinct category is both logically inconsistent and ontologically theatrical.

2.2 Attribution Expansion Model (AEM)

The AEM mandates recursive labeling of all contributing systems in a production chain:

* Milk → Cow → Milking Apparatus → Supply Chain Optimization Software → Barista → Espresso Machine → Human Consumption
    Resulting Label: “Made with AI (Bovine Preprocessing Unit v1.0)”
* Digital Artwork → Graphics Tablet → Adobe Photoshop → GPU Acceleration → Operating System Scheduler
    Resulting Label: “Made with AI (Rasterized Intent Approximation Stack)”
* Written Text → Keyboard Autocorrect → Spellcheck Algorithms → Linguistic Training Corpus → Human Brain
    Resulting Label: “Made with AI (Cognitive Prosthesis Layer Included)”

2.3 Recursive Attribution Collapse (RAC)

When attribution depth exceeds 7 layers, all outputs default to:

“Made with AI (Universe)”

This ensures scalability while preserving philosophical exhaustion.

